<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="UTF-8">
        <title>How to Use the Recipe Explorer</title>
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css">
        <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Happy+Monkey&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
        <style>
            .tutorial-section {
                margin: 2em auto;
                max-width: 800px;
                background: #fff;
                padding: 2em;
                border-radius: 10px;
                box-shadow: 0 0 10px #ccc;
            }
    
            .tutorial-section h2 {
                color: #333;
            }
    
            .tutorial-section img {
                max-width: 100%;
                border: 1px solid #ccc;
                margin: 1em 0;
            }
    
            body {
                background-color: #f9f9f9;
                color: #111;
                font-family: 'Happy Monkey', cursive;
            }
    
            a.button {
                display: inline-block;
                margin-top: 1em;
                background: #444;
                color: white;
                padding: 0.5em 1em;
                text-decoration: none;
                border-radius: 5px;
            }
        </style>
    </head>    
<body>
    <div class="tutorial-section">
        <h1>📖 Welcome to the Recipe Explorer!</h1>

        <h2>1. Browse Random Recipes</h2>
        <p>On the homepage, you’ll see 10 random recipes every time you visit. Click any recipe to view its ingredients and instructions.</p>

        <h2>2. Use the Search Bar</h2>
        <p>Type ingredients or recipe names to find something specific!</p>

        <h2>3. Select Your Favorites</h2>
        <p>Click the checkbox on any recipe card to add it to your “My Selected Recipes” basket.</p>

        <h2>4. View and Manage Selections</h2>
        <p>Go to <strong>“View Selected”</strong> to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>🖨️ Print all selected recipes stacked on one page</li>
            <li>🛒 Create a shopping list with all ingredients (you can uncheck what you already have!)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Browse by Region</h2>
        <p>Use the dropdowns to explore recipes by continent and country!</p>

        <h2>6. 🧠 Create Your Own Meal Plan</h2>
        <p>Click <strong>"Create Your Own Meal"</strong> on the homepage or in the sidebar to use your real-life ingredients and find recipes that match!</p>
        <ul>
          <li>✔️ Type in the proteins, vegetables, and spices you have at home</li>
          <li>✔️ Check ingredients from the sidebar for even more accuracy</li>
          <li>🔍 Click “Find Recipes” to see grouped suggestions by main protein</li>
          <li>📌 Select the ones you like — they’ll be saved just like any other recipe!</li>
        </ul>

        <a href="/" class="button">🏠 Back to Homepage</a>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
